Sasini of Kenya Extends Retreat as Tea Auction Prices Decline

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-03-30T11:36:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/sasini-of-kenya-extends-retreat-as-tea-auction-prices-decline.html
Sasini Ltd. (STCL) , a Kenyan tea and
coffee grower, dropped for a second day after tea prices fell at
the world’s biggest auction.  The stock declined 2.2 percent to 9 shillings as of 2:02
p.m. local time, adding to yesterday’s 1.6 percent retreat and
pushing its year-to-date fall to 31 percent.  African tea prices retreated to an average of $2.70 per
kilogram at a sale in the Kenyan port city of  Mombasa  this week,
Tea Brokers East Africa Ltd. said in an e-mailed report today.
The leaves sold for an average of $2.77 a kilogram last week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
